The paper deals with text matching and entity resolution, which are common topics in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), suggesting that cs.CL and cs.IR are likely sub-categories. The paper also focuses on developing a model for business data analytics, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning (ML) and data mining, making cs.LG and cs.DB possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a deep learning model that encodes text at the character level, which is a common technique in NLP and ML, indicating that cs.AI is also a possible sub-category.
